data.name: allnex
data.description: allnex is a specialty chemicals pioneer and a leading producer of coating resins and additives for architectural, industrial, protective, automotive and special purpose coatings and inks. We serve our customers with a global footprint that provides a reliable supply of resins and additives, responsive local customer support and a track record of innovation. We believe strongly in working safely and protecting the environment by using energy more efficiently, increasing the amount of renewable and recycled content in our products and reducing waste.

data.name: EBECRYL
data.description: 100% solids UV curable resins monomers and oligomers, including a wide range of urethane acrylates, polyester acrylates, amino acrylates and epoxy acrylates.

data.name: CYMEL
data.description:
CYMEL® amino crosslinkers have been used for over 50 years in metal, wood and rubber coating applications, including automotive OEM, kitchen cabinets, metal food and beverage packaging, metal building products, tire and general metal finishing. 
The crosslinkers are used with epoxy, polyester, acrylic and alkyd resins and provide the desired balance of flexibility, exterior durability, chemical resistance and film toughness. Our new CYMEL® NF formaldehyde-free crosslinkers are ideal for applications where formaldehyde emissions are a concern. 
The CYMEL® amino resin crosslinker line includes:

Methylated and butylated melamines
Alkylated and imino mixed ether melamines
Alkylated ureas
Formaldehyde-free modified ureas
Benzoguanamine
Glycoluril

data.name: BECKOPOX
data.description: Waterborne epoxy dispersion and epoxy hardener for lower-VOC, high-performance anticorrosion industrial and construction coatings

data.name: PHENODUR
data.description:
PHENODUR® phenolic resins mainly find use in industrial and packaging coatings, in combination with other types of resins, such as epoxies, acrylics and polyesters.
PHENODUR®specially formulated solvent-based and waterborne resins are designed for use in coatings applied to the interior of metal food containers, and include phenolic resin systems that can be used to make Bisphenol A- and BADGE-free interior can coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL
data.description: Coating additives help formulators optimize paint processing, appearance, application and stability.

data.name: CYCAT
data.description: This catalyst portfolio encompasses a portfolio of weak acid, strong acid and block catalyst materials designed to work with specific amino resin types and coating systems. Catalysts to speed up cross linking reactions of amino or phenolic resin cured stoving enamels or two-component polyurethane systems.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 255 N
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 255 N, a proficient dispersant and wetting agent, elevates coatings in solvent-borne, solventless, and high-solids formulations. ADDITOL® XL 255 N proudly claims to be APEO-free, bio-based, and tin-free. Its special properties include reducing flocculation with common organic and inorganic pigments, enhancing color strength and gloss in air drying, and stoving paint systems. With its effective wetting and dispersing capabilities, ADDITOL® XL 255 N not only shortens pigment grinding time but also prevents the settling of pigments and extenders.

data.name: MODAFLOW® 2100
data.description: MODAFLOW® 2100 is a clear to light yellow coating primarily designed for the automotive, transportation, and paints and coatings sectors. It finds extensive applications in automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, vehicle refinishing, and building and construction wood finishes. The product's versatility extends to various printing and packaging segments, including flexography, gravure printing, inkjet printing, offset, and lithographic printing. Additionally, it offers compatibility with substrates like metal and wood, and its cure method involves radiation.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXL 4950
data.description: ADDITOL® VXL 4950 is a specialized adhesion-promoting primer formulated for plastics, specifically designed for application as a pre-treatment primer. It is crucial to note that ADDITOL® VXL 4950 is not intended for use as an additive in paints. With a focus on marine coatings, this primer enhances adhesion when applied before the coating process. Its application methods include brush, roller, and spray, ensuring versatility in different coating scenarios. The appearance of ADDITOL® VXL 4950 is clear, contributing to its suitability for various plastic substrates in marine coating applications.

data.name: MODAFLOW® 9200
data.description: MODAFLOW® 9200 is an APEO-free, tin-free, and VOC-free clearcoat technology suitable for various markets, including automotive and transportation, paints and coatings, as well as printing and packaging. It finds applications in automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, vehicle refinish, wood coatings and finishes, coil coatings, industrial coatings, metal coatings, packaging coatings, and printing inks such as flexography, gravure, inkjet, lithographic, and screen printing. This radiation-curable coating is compatible with metal and wood substrates, presenting a clear appearance and utilizing radiation cure as its cure method.

data.name: SETAQUA® PU F125
data.description: SETAQUA® PU F125 is intended for 1K (1 component) aqueous coatings and is especially suited for use in roofing and building envelope applications in the building and construction sector. Perfect for wood substrate insulation projects and Exterior Insulation and Finish Systems (EIFS). This clear liquid coating is a dependable solution for wood surfaces, blending invisibly with waterborne compositions. Its wood-compatibility guarantees a reliable and effective application procedure.

data.name: MODAFLOW® RESIN
data.description: MODAFLOW® RESIN is an acrylic flow modifier specifically formulated without the addition of silicone. It finds application in non-aqueous industrial coatings and powder coatings, where its primary functions include enhancing flow and leveling, reducing issues like pinholes, fisheyes, craters, and orange peel. This product contributes to improved substrate wetting and helps maintain or enhance substrate adhesion. Additionally, MODAFLOW® RESIN serves as a defoaming agent, aids in air release, and facilitates pigment dispersion. It is employed in various coating applications such as top coats, powder coatings, radiation-curable coatings, clearcoats, screen printing inks, inkjet inks, varnishes, flexography inks, solventborne coatings, gravure inks, and lithographic inks. Notably, it adheres to labeling claims of being VOC-free, APEO-free, and Tin-free.

data.name: BECKOPOX™ EH 694
data.description: BECKOPOX™ EH 694, categorized under CASE Ingredients additives, functions as a hardening agent from the anhydride chemical family. Notably VOC-free, it offers enhanced heat and chemical resistance. Designed for diverse coating applications, including industrial, furniture, metal, and specialty coatings, it's compatible with epoxies and hybrid systems. Available in granules, liquids, and solid forms, it caters to epoxy, hybrid, and powder coating formulations.

data.name: EBECRYL® 303
data.description: EBECRYL® 303, crafted by CASE Ingredients, is a cutting-edge product tailored for paints and coatings and the printing and packaging sectors. Notably Bisphenol A-free and boasting a low carbon footprint, this solvent-free and VOC-free liquid is optimized for applications like film and foil coatings and overprint varnishes. Its versatility shines in printing techniques such as flexography, gravure, inkjet, and screen printing, especially on plastic substrates. With efficient curtain and gravure coating methods, it ensures rapid radiation curing, delivering a clear and impeccable finish.

data.name: CYCAT® 4045 Catalyst
data.description: CYCAT® 4045 Catalyst, categorized under CASE Ingredients' additives, is specifically formulated to cater to the demands of the automotive, transportation, and marine coatings sectors. Offered in a clear liquid state, this catalyst is designed to seamlessly integrate with metal substrates, ensuring an efficient and effective application process.

data.description: ADDITOL® XL 255 N, a proficient dispersant and wetting agent, elevates coatings in solvent-borne, solventless, and high-solids formulations. ADDITOL® XL 255 N proudly claims to be APEO-free, bio-based, and tin-free. Its special properties include reducing flocculation with common organic and inorganic pigments, enhancing color strength and gloss in air drying, and stoving paint systems. With its effective wetting and dispersing capabilities, ADDITOL® XL 255 N not only shortens pigment grinding time but also prevents the settling of pigments and extenders.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXL 4950
data.description: ADDITOL® VXL 4950 is a specialized adhesion-promoting primer formulated for plastics, specifically designed for application as a pre-treatment primer. It is crucial to note that ADDITOL® VXL 4950 is not intended for use as an additive in paints. With a focus on marine coatings, this primer enhances adhesion when applied before the coating process. Its application methods include brush, roller, and spray, ensuring versatility in different coating scenarios. The appearance of ADDITOL® VXL 4950 is clear, contributing to its suitability for various plastic substrates in marine coating applications.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6208
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6208 is a polymer non-ionic dispersing additive specifically designed for grinding both inorganic and organic pigments in water or waterborne formulations such as alkyd resin, acrylic, epoxy, and urethane emulsions. As a dispersant, it plays a crucial role in achieving a uniform and stable dispersion of pigments within the coating system. Its versatility extends to various applications, including automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, vehicle refinish, decorative paints, wood coatings, and finishes.

data.name: ADDITOL® P 964
data.description: ADDITOL® P 964, a versatile catalyst, stands as a VOC-free and TMA-free solution for hybrid coating and epoxy coating applications. With compatibility extending to epoxy (EP), this product is designed to enhance the curing process and overall performance of coatings. Targeted for use in the building and construction sector, particularly in decorative paints, ADDITOL® P 964 ensures optimal results and reliability in various coating formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® LED 01
data.description: ADDITOL® LED 01 is a transparent liquid primarily designed for the paints and coatings sector, specifically targeting the automotive and transportation industries. It finds its application in various segments such as automotive OEM coatings, rail, mass transit coatings, aerospace coatings, and marine coatings. This product is formulated to be compatible with metal substrates and surfaces.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 6577
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 6577 is a solvent-borne coating additive, boasting features such as high sagging resistance, high pigment loading, and a glossy finish. Notably, it aligns with labeling claims of being organotin-free and tin-free. This additive finds diverse applications, including automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, vehicle refinish, decorative paints, coil coatings, industrial coatings, and metal coatings. Its multifunctional characteristics make it a versatile choice for various coating needs.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6393
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6393 emerges as an innovative solution, proudly boasting claims of being NMP-free, APEO-free, and tin-free. Notable features encompass high film thickness and improved degassing. Distinguished by its milder smell compared to Additol VXW 6392, it holds an advantageous position in hazard qualification. Tailored for paints and coatings applications, particularly automotive OEM coatings and marine coatings, ADDITOL® VXW 6393 stands as a progressive choice, ensuring superior performance, reduced environmental impact, and enhanced safety qualifications.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6210 N
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6210 N is a silicone-modified defoamer designed for emulsion paints, alkyd resin emulsion paints, and waterborne two-component epoxy paints. This highly effective defoamer exhibits excellent emulsification in water, ensuring easy incorporation into various waterborne paint systems. Specifically recommended for low and medium-viscosity paints, including gloss and silky gloss emulsion paints, as well as coatings for parquet floors and furniture based on acrylate and acrylate/polyurethane emulsions.

data.name: ADDITOL® CPK
data.description: ADDITOL® CPK is a white crystalline substance tailored for markets such as automotive and transportation, paints and coatings, and printing and packaging. Ideal for automotive OEM coatings, building finishes, and industrial coatings, it exhibits compatibility with metal, plastic, and wood substrates. Designed as a top coat, this product upholds Bisphenol A-free, solvent-free, and VOC-free labeling claims.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6394
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6394 is a versatile formulation that serves as a dispersant and wetting agent. Tailored for a range of applications, including screen printing ink, inkjet ink, waterborne coating, flexography ink, gravel ink, and primer, it proudly claims to be APEO-free and tin-free. Notable features include high gloss, high pigment loading, low reactivity, and wet-on-Wet properties. With applications spanning paints and coatings, especially automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, and vehicle refinish, ADDITOL® VXW 6394 stands as a comprehensive choice, ensuring optimal performance across various printing and coating formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 6591
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 6591 is a water-dilutable, modified polyester-acrylate polymer designed for use as a grinding aid in color- and shading pigment pastes. This additive exhibits compatibility with various coating systems, including waterborne air-drying and stoving alkyds, waterborne acrylic resins, UV-curing systems, PU dispersions, and plastic dispersions. It functions as a grinding aid, aiding in the dispersion of pigments. ADDITOL® XW 6591 is suitable for applications on metal and wood substrates.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 480
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 480 a specialized leveling agent, stands out as a monomer-free, NMP-free, APEO-free, and tin-free solution. Tailored for clearcoat applications, it boasts features like overbake resistance, improved edge coverage, low migration, high gloss, improved dullness, low reactivity, high temperature-curing, wet-on-Wet properties, and improved flexibility. Its special properties position it as an additive dedicated to enhancing the surface quality of paint films, especially in automotive coatings. The versatile applications of ADDITOL® XL 480 extend to the automotive and transportation sectors, encompassing automotive OEM coatings and marine coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 4940 N
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 4940 N is a lead-free combination drier designed for water-dilutable applications, serving as a drying agent for oxidatively drying alkyd resin paints and acryl-alkyd hybrid systems. Widely applicable in automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, decorative paints, wood coatings and finishes, and offset and lithographic printing, it enhances hardness and reactivity in formulations. Notably, it is labeled as tin-free, formaldehyde-free, NMP-free, and monomer-free, aligning with considerations for safer and environmentally friendly coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 180
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 180, a formidable coupling agent and adhesion promoter, redefines coating formulations. With claims of being APEO-free and monomer-free, this product stands out in paints and coatings applications, specifically automotive, transportation, and marine coatings. Its impressive features, including high pigment loading, corrosion resistance, improved chemical resistance, good metal flake orientation, high temperature curing, and high reactivity, ensure elevated performance.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 330
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 330, a specialized dispersant and wetting agent, is formulated to excel in aqueous systems. Proudly APEO-free, tin-free, and solvent-free, ADDITOL® XW 330 exhibits environmental compatibility. With special properties as a wetting and dispersing agent for inorganic pigments and extenders, as well as the ability to stabilize emulsion paints and prevent thickening, ADDITOL® XW 330 offers a versatile solution. Notably, it is specifically designed for use in non-glossy emulsion paints. For applications requiring silky and high-gloss emulsion paints, ADDITOL® VXW 6200 is recommended. The distinguishing features of ADDITOL® XW 330 make it a valuable choice for achieving optimal results in various non-glossy emulsion paint formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® DRY CF100
data.description: ADDITOL® DRY CF100 is a light, cloudy additive designed for various sectors, including automotive and transportation, paints and coatings, and printing and packaging. Notably APEO-free and cobalt-free, it finds applications in automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, decorative paints, and industrial coatings. This additive is compatible with substrates like metal and wood, offering versatility in both solventborne and waterborne coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 270
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 270, a liquid powerhouse, serves as a wetting agent, rheology modifier, and thickener. Proudly claiming to be tin-free, bio-based, and APEO-free, this product is tailored for solventless and high-solids coating and solvent-borne coating applications. With special properties that prevent pigment sedimentation, enhance pigment-wetting during dispersion, and prevent pigment from floating in mixtures, ADDITOL® XL 270 is a comprehensive solution. It reduces the tendency to flow off, improving the coverage of edges in many paint systems.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXL 6237 N
data.description: ADDITOL® VXL 6237 N is a clear product tailored for the paints and coatings sector, especially within the automotive and transportation markets. This benzyl alcohol-free, bisphenol A-free, and formaldehyde-free formulation is well-suited for applications like automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, and wood coatings and finishes. Additionally, it caters to inkjet printing in the printing and packaging segment, specifically designed for metal and wood substrates. The appearance of this product is transparent, serving both the industrial and transportation sectors.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 6568
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 6568, a cutting-edge solution, brings a host of benefits as an APEO-free and bio-based formulation. With features like corrosion resistance, faster cycle time, good peel, high film thickness, and high gloss, it stands out in coatings. Its special properties make it an excellent addition to stripping enamels as an anti-adhesion promotor, offering temporary protection against mechanical attack and corrosion to various substrates. Notably, it can be utilized in both solvent-based and aqueous systems.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6206
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6206 serves as an emulsified combination drier, free from nonylphenylethoxylate, and blends cobalt, lithium, and zirconium. Designed for waterborne oxidatively drying alkyd resin paints, it functions as a siccative. Particularly well-suited for externally emulsified alkyd resin emulsions, it supports the drying process. The key function lies in facilitating the drying of coatings. It is essential to note that ADDITOL® VXW 6206 is labeled as monomer-free, formaldehyde-free, NMP-free, and tin-free, aligning with specific requirements and considerations for environmentally friendly and safe coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 6533
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 6533, a dedicated drying agent, is formulated to excel in various coating applications, including primer, top coat, and waterborne coating. With claims of being tin-free, APEO-free, and cobalt-free, this product aligns with environmental considerations. Notable features, including improved water spotting, improved hardness, corrosion resistance, faster cycle time, low temperature curing, outdoor durability, and improved water immersion, make ADDITOL® XW 6533 a versatile and efficient solution. Its applications extend to the automotive and transportation sectors, covering automotive OEM coatings and marine coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXL 4992
data.description: ADDITOL® VXL 4992 functions as a wetting and dispersing agent specifically designed for high-body UP knifing fillers and glass fiber-reinforced pigmented polyesters. Its role is crucial in enhancing pigment wetting, leading to a shortened dispersion time. Additionally, it contributes to viscosity reduction, allowing for increased pigment and filler concentration. The agent also improves air release properties, providing better leveling and flow characteristics in the final product.

data.name: ADDITOL® TPO
data.description: ADDITOL® TPO is a yellow powder clearcoat designed for the paints and coatings sector, particularly emphasizing applications in automotive OEM coatings, wood coatings and finishes, and industrial coatings. This product, labeled as bisphenol A-free, solvent-free, and VOC-free, caters to markets including automotive and transportation, paints and coatings, and printing and packaging. It demonstrates compatibility specifically with wood substrates, offering a solid physical form.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 390
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 390 serves as a silicone-free flow and wetting agent designed for waterborne coating systems. It effectively prevents flow defects in various waterborne coatings and enhances substrate wetting. This APEO-free, formaldehyde-free, and tin-free formulation is compatible with epoxies (EP). Noteworthy features include improved edge coverage, long wave reduction, wet-on-wet properties, short wave reduction, and low migration. Widely applicable, it finds use in enamel, waterborne coating, and epoxy coating applications.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 372 N
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 372 N, tailored for waterborne coating applications, stands as a testament to innovation. ADDITOL® XW 372 N proudly claims to be NMP-free, APEO-free, and tin-free, emphasizing its commitment to environmental considerations. Boasting features such as high popping limit and low blistering, ADDITOL® XW 372 N ensures optimal performance and quality in coatings. Its applications extend to the automotive and transportation sectors, including automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, and vehicle refinish formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 6580
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 6580 is a leveling and substrate wetting agent formulated with a polyether-modified siloxane, suitable for both waterborne and solvent-borne paint systems. This additive is designed to reduce surface tension effectively, leading to improved substrate wetting and leveling, without contributing to foam stabilization. It is labeled as tin-free, monomer-free, and APEO-free. ADDITOL® XW 6580 offers features such as circulation stability, wet-on-wet properties, multi-substrate adhesion, improved edge coverage, low film thickness, improved long-wave reduction, and reduced surface preparation. It finds applications in solvent-borne coatings, clearcoats, and waterborne coatings.

data.name: ADDITOL® XW 6565
data.description: ADDITOL® XW 6565 stands out as a multifunctional universal grinding medium crafted for optimal performance in solvent-based, water-based, and low VOC decorative paints. Its distinctive composition offers several advantages, including exceptional color development, effective viscosity control, and stabilization with a wide range of architectural pigments. Additionally, this formulation enhances humidity and water resistance, contributing to the overall durability and longevity of the painted surface.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6388
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6388 is a dynamic solution that excels as a rheology modifier and thickener. Tailored for waterborne coating and primer formulations, it is NMP-free and APEO-free. Noteworthy features encompass corrosion resistance, high film thickness, high sagging resistance, and improved edge coverage. With its special properties as a urethane-modified polyether, it exhibits a substantial thickening effect in the middle shear range. Applications extend across paints and coatings, including automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, and vehicle refinish, making ADDITOL® VXW 6388 an indispensable component for achieving optimal performance and durability in coating formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6386
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6386 emerges as a key player in waterproof coating, enamel, and 2K (2-component) coating formulations. Its standout features include being tin-free, NMP-free, and APEO-free, coupled with high film thickness and a high popping limit. This easy-emulsifiable defoamer addresses the challenges posed by conventional mineral-oil or silicon-based counterparts, ensuring heightened surface quality by preventing issues like orange peel and craters, especially in high-quality waterborne systems.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 250
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 250, a dynamic dispersant and wetting agent, stands out with its versatile applications in solventborne and waterborne coating formulations. This product proudly claims to be APEO-free, bio-based, and tin-free. Its special properties include reducing dispersing time, enhancing gloss and leveling, and effective compatibility with all pigments used in air drying and stoving solvent-borne paints, as well as water-dilutable paint systems.

data.name: ADDITOL® HDMAP
data.description: ADDITOL® HDMAP is a clear yellow liquid designed for the automotive and transportation, paints and coatings, and printing and packaging markets. This solvent-free and VOC-free additive is especially tailored for automotive OEM coatings, wood coatings and finishes, and industrial coatings. With compatibility across metal, plastic, and wood substrates, it serves as an effective clearcoat and topcoat solution.

data.name: ADDITOL® XL 186
data.description: ADDITOL® XL 186, a powerful coupling agent and adhesion promoter, redefines coating formulations. With claims of being APEO-free and monomer-free, this product stands out in paint and coating applications. Notable features include high pigment loading, improved mechanical resistance, corrosion resistance, improved chemical resistance, chip resistance, good metal flake orientation, high temperature curing, high reactivity, high impact resistance, and improved edge coverage. A unique characteristic lies in its ability to enhance the adhesion of stoving enamels and fast-drying air-drying paints to sheet iron, particularly intercoat adhesion in multi-coat paint systems.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6208/60
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6208/60 is a polymeric non-ionic dispersing and wetting additive tailored for solvent-borne, solvent-free, and water-dilutable paint systems. This versatile additive contributes to improved gloss levels and stabilizes the achieved degree of gloss in the final coating. Notably, it exhibits the ability to reduce viscosity, which is particularly beneficial in high-filled paint systems. The product finds application in various formulations, including the production of binder-free pigment pastes and tinting base colors. In particular, ADDITOL® VXW 6208/60 serves as a wetting agent in solvent-free and solvent-borne two-pack epoxy systems, demonstrating its adaptability across different paint formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXL 6212
data.description: ADDITOL® VXL 6212 is a cationic, highly molecular resin-like wetting agent designed to enhance the dispersion and wetting properties of both inorganic and organic pigments in formulations. This versatile additive is well-suited for a range of coatings, including automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, vehicle refinish, and industrial coatings. Notably, ADDITOL® VXL 6212 aligns with eco-friendly considerations, being labeled as bisphenol A-free, formaldehyde-free, and benzyl alcohol-free. Its medium viscous liquid form ensures ease of incorporation into various formulations.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6396
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6396 is a multifaceted solution that excels as a flow promoter, leveling agent, and flow modifier in a variety of applications. Tailored for clearcoat, screen printing ink, inkjet ink, waterborne coating, varnishes, flexography ink, and gravel ink, it proudly claims to be NMP-free, APEO-free, and tin-free. Standout features include reduced overspray, improved edge coverage, improved long wave reduction, low film thickness, improved short wave reduction, reduced surface preparation, and wet-on-wet properties. With applications spanning paints and coatings, especially automotive OEM coatings, marine coatings, and vehicle refinish.

data.name: ADDITOL® VXW 6503 N
data.description: ADDITOL® VXW 6503 N is a leveling and substrate wetting agent formulated with a polyether-modified polysiloxane, designed for waterborne paint systems. It effectively reduces surface tension, enhancing substrate wetting and leveling in the absence of foam stabilization. Notably, ADDITOL® VXW 6503 N maintains surface slip and does not impact recoatability. This formulation delivers improved performance in waterborne paint applications, making it a valuable addition for achieving optimal wetting and leveling characteristics without compromising other essential properties.
